early menapause perimenapause premenapause whatever it's called i am years old no children had farely normal periods most my life with the exception of a week off here and there last time i went this long missing my period was years ago so here i am years later no period for months now feels like it's coming then it doesnt and it comes and goes i am not pregnant for sure i hadn't thought of the menapause thing considering i am only but i noticed that i was getting hot really fast like only after a few minutes of cleaning house i start to get hot so if this is so are there health concerns ahead of me any doctors out there it's called perimenopause which is the stage before real menopause hits which could be several years before it sounds more like a hormone imbalance hormones will give you hot flashes even when menopause isn't the issue just ask pregnant women or pmsing women it's not normal to go months without bleeding at this point you really should go in for a hormone analysis if one of them is off they can give you meds to fix it also have them check your thyroid function a hypo hyperactive thyroid will throw off your cycles as well good luck Menstrual cycle Pregnancy Fertility awareness In vitro fertilisation Menopause Infertility Endometriosis Miscarriage Chronic fatigue syndrome Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Prostate cancer Hall & Oates Urinary incontinence Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Thyroid Breastfeeding Amiodarone Acne Breast cancer Puberty Endometrial cancer Jet engine Nutrition Phoebe Halliwell Poker jargon Congenital hypothyroidism Cancer Polycystic ovary syndrome Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Childbirth Prolactinoma Coeliac disease Turner syndrome Amenorrhoea Daryl Hall Migraine Osteoporosis EastEnders Progesterone Human height Episodes of Lost (Season 1) History of intersex surgery Obstetrics Oral contraceptive Hypopituitarism Sexual dysfunction Hormone replacement therapy Hypothyroidism CPU cache Hypoglycemia Stuttering Abortion debate En